Initialize the Time Engine (QTimer)

Import and set up a QTimer. This is a PySide6 tool that triggers a function automatically every second (or any interval you choose).

Create the Time Display (QLabel)

Make a large, centered label that starts by displaying "25:00" (for a 25-minute focus session).

Build the Controls (QHBoxLayout)

Create three buttons: "Start", "Pause", and "Reset".

State Management Logic

Connect "Start" to begin the QTimer. Connect "Pause" to stop it. Connect "Reset" to change the time back to 25:00 and stop the timer.

Countdown Math

Write a function that triggers every time the QTimer ticks (every 1 second). This function needs to subtract 1 second from the total time, format it back into "Minutes:Seconds", and update the QLabel.
